('construction-cost-data', 'CCD-08', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '["CCD-11"]', 'Backward mining COMPLETED: fetched the full KfW/IWU evaluation PDF directly (sanitaerwirtschaft.de mirror; pypdf/pdfminer text extraction after fixing a broken cryptography/cffi binding in the sandbox), located the real Literaturverzeichnis, and extracted genuine citations. 4 relevant sources inserted (REF-00834..00837): Hackmann/Schüssler/Schmutz 2014 age-appropriate housing-adaptation potential analysis, Prognos 2014 predecessor KfW programme evaluation, Gerste 2015 domestic-falls cost-benefit, Edinger/Lerch/Lentze 2007 ''Barrierearm'' concept paper. Many other bibliography entries (burglary victimology, general demographics, labor market) were excluded as out of scope per the relevance filter. Forward mining: no DOI/ISBN, no citation-graph connector for this grey-literature report — DEFERRED.', '2026-07-19T23:46:41Z', 'session_2026-07-19-citation-mining-nonenglish-batch1', '2026-07-20 00:03', 'session_2026-07-19-citation-mining-nonenglish-batch4-pdf', NULL),
('wayfinding-dementia-spatial-design', 'WDS-11', NULL, NULL, 1, 0, '["WDS-24"]', 'Backward mining via WebFetch of the guideline page (not DOI-based; source has no DOI — Norwegian Helsedirektoratet clinical guideline). Confirmed and inserted REF-00797 (Landmark et al 2009, FHI Report 11-2009, systematic knowledge summary on dementia housing design). Guideline also names REDIC 2015 registry findings, Dalsbø et al 2014, Dahm et al 2014 (FHI Report 27-2014), and a SINTEF 2015 report (''Er smått alltid godt i demensomsorgen'') as further leads — not verified/inserted this pass (SINTEF site returned HTTP 403; the FHI items were not independently re-fetched). Forward mining: no DOI/PMID, no forward-citation connector for non-indexed Norwegian grey literature — DEFERRED.', '2026-07-19 23:46', 'session_2026-07-19-citation-mining-nonenglish-batch1', '2026-07-19T23:46:20Z', 'session_2026-07-19-citation-mining-nonenglish-batch1', NULL);
